***NOTE***

I have not tried theese all theese instructions as i already
have virtual env, pip and pyhon installed. Please update this document
if you find anything that is wrong.

To run the Gherkin tests the following is required:
    
    Python 2.7
    pip
    virtualenv

To install on debian (as root):
    
    apt-get install python-dev python-setuptools
    easy_install virtualenv

To create the python virtual environment:
    
    virtualenv --no-site-packages testenv

To enter the python virtual environment:
    
    source testenv/bin/activate

To install the dependencies (inside the virtual env):
    
    pip install -r requirements.txt

To run the tests (inside the virtual env):
    
    lettuce

To leave the virtual environment:
    
    deactivate
